"arabic","text_bw":"zinobaArN","text_ar":"زِنْبَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K,) a dial. var. mentioned by ISk: (S:) [being a coll. gen. n.,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"znbwr","text_ar":"زنبور"},{"kind":"text","text":"is [sometimes] made of the fem. gender: the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zanaAbiyru","text_ar":"زَنَابِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alz~anaAbiyru","text_ar":"الزَّنَابِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"sometimes means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the flies of the meadows"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gardens"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ubaAbu Alr~awoDi","text_ar":"ذُبَابُ الرَّوْضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"). (Ham p. 324.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A young ass that is able to bear burdens."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A large rat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zanaAbiru","text_ar":"زَنَابِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", occurring in poetry [app. for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zanaAbiyru","text_ar":"زَنَابِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b4-  Also, [as an epithet,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Light,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"active; clever,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ingenious;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) mentioned by Abu-l-Jarráh, from a man of the Benoo-Kiláb, and he adds that it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"active;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quick in reply;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zunoburN","text_ar":"زُنْبُرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)       -A2-  Also, and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zinbiyrN","text_ar":"زِنبِيرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zinobaArN","text_ar":"زِنْبَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain tree,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of large size,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resembling the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dulob","text_ar":"دُلْب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plane-tree"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"but not wide, the leaves of which are like those of the nut-tree in appearance and scent, having blossoms like those of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu$ar","text_ar":"عُشَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"white tinged"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with another colour"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and having a fruit exactly like the olive, which, when fully ripe, becomes intensely black and very sweet, and is eaten by men like ripe dates, has a stone like that of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gubayoraA='","text_ar":"غُبَيْرَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fruit of the service-tree"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and dyes the mouth like as does the mulberry: it is planted."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  Also, the same three words,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A species of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tiyn","text_ar":"تِين"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fig"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"called by the people of the towns and villages the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tiyn HulowaAniY~","text_ar":"تِين حُلْوَانِىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (IAar, K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of the strange trees of the desert:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zanaAbiyru","text_ar":"زَنَابِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IAar, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}